My &lt;a href="http://www.csiro.au/helix/mathsbyemail/newsletter.html"&gt;maths by mail&lt;/a&gt; subscription just notified me that this Thursday is considered&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pi_Day"&gt;pi day&lt;/a&gt; in Australia (22/7 rather than 3.14). I am used to celebrating in March, but I am glad to hear that we can justify celebrating twice a year.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Unfortunately, there seems to be only one day that we can celebrate as&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="http://tauday.com/"&gt;tau day&lt;/a&gt;, and only one day for &lt;a href="http://letsplaymath.net/2010/02/05/heads-up-for-e-day/"&gt;celebrating e&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
